Question: Suggest ways to optimize the code in the given block.
for(int i=0;i<=n;i++){
    if(i%2==0){
        System.out.println(i);
    }
} Answer: One way to optimize this code is to reduce the number of iterations by starting the loop at 2 and incrementing i by 2 in each step, as even numbers start from 2. This can be achieved by changing the loop statement to:

for(int i=2; i<=n; i+=2)

Another optimization could be to use a while loop instead of a for loop and precompute the limit of the loop outside the loop, like this:

int i = 0;
int limit = (n % 2 == 0) ? n : n-1;
while(i <= limit){
    System.out.println(i);
    i += 2;
}

This way, we only need to perform the modulo operation once, and the loop will not iterate unnecessarily.

